質問: 1. What are the causes of air pollution and water pollution in many big cities? 2. What measures can be taken to improve the situation?
答え: 1. The causes of air pollution and water pollution in many big cities are mainly industrial emissions, automobile exhaust gases, pesticides, chemical fertilizers, fuel use, deforestation, urban expansion, population growth, and improper wastewater treatment.
2. The following measures can be taken to improve the situation.
・Strengthen regulations to reduce industrial emissions and automobile exhaust gases.
・Reduce the use of pesticides and chemical fertilizers.
・Reduce fuel use.
・Reduce deforestation.
・Reduce urban expansion.
・Reduce population growth.
・Improve improper wastewater treatment.
